{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60/comments/60792123.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake:61847d89595c..c5f1c35a73f6?path=config%2Fignition-cmake-config.cmake.in"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-60792123"}}, "parent": {"id": 60699342, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60/comments/60699342.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60/_/diff#comment-60699342"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 60, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/60.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/60"}}, "title": "Adding cppcheck and cpplint with codecheck target"}, "content": {"raw": "I was reading the following documentation about creating relocatable packages:\n\n* https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.5/manual/cmake-packages.7.html#creating-relocatable-packages\n\nThere are places where it says to use relative paths rather than absolute paths when specifying include directories, but I wasn't sure if it applies to other paths as well.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I was reading the following documentation about creating relocatable packages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.5/manual/cmake-packages.7.html#creating-relocatable-packages\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.5/manual/cmake-packages.7.html#creating-relocatable-packages</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are places where it says to use relative paths rather than absolute paths when specifying include directories, but I wasn't sure if it applies to other paths as well.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-04-05T16:40:17.215969+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "